244
00:12:32,952 --> 00:12:34,520
<i>Yet why, again...</i>

245
00:12:35,054 --> 00:12:36,990
<i>do</i> <i>I</i> <i>feel</i> <i>this</i> <i>stirring</i>
<i>in</i> <i>my</i> <i>heart?</i>

246
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:39,459
<i>I want more!</i>

247
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:41,227
<i>I want him to torment me more!</i>

248
00:12:42,795 --> 00:12:45,031
What' in the world is wrong
with this girl?

249
00:12:48,301 --> 00:12:49,035
Man!

250
00:12:49,035 --> 00:12:52,338
You didn't put your foot down, so now
she really does plan on staying here,

251
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:53,106
doesn't she!

252
00:12:53,239 --> 00:12:56,409
Isn't it about time that you showed her
how much a man you really are?

253
00:12:56,743 --> 00:12:58,978
But I really did try to show her that.

254
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:02,749
<i>That man has already fallen</i>
<i>under my spell.</i>

255
00:13:03,349 --> 00:13:05,118
<i>Men are such stupid creatures,</i>

256
00:13:06,252 --> 00:13:10,123
<i>but what is this occasional throbbing</i>
<i>of my heart I'm feeling?</i>

257
00:13:13,326 --> 00:13:14,327
I'm back everyone!

258
00:13:14,827 --> 00:13:16,729
Oh?
Gin, do you think that she's...?

259
00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:17,930
No don't tell me?

260
00:13:18,064 --> 00:13:18,765
What?

261
00:13:18,765 --> 00:13:19,666
Me?

262
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:21,167
No there's...

263
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:22,268
there's just no way.

264
00:13:26,773 --> 00:13:27,507
Hello, who is it?

265
00:13:27,774 --> 00:13:29,208
This is Sacchan speaking.

266
00:13:29,442 --> 00:13:31,444
<i>Hello there, Miss Assassin.</i>

267
00:13:31,444 --> 00:13:32,578
Who are you?

268
00:13:32,745 --> 00:13:34,447
<i>Nice to meet you last night.</i>

269
00:13:34,447 --> 00:13:37,116
<i>I'm so glad to hear your voice again.</i>

270
00:13:37,116 --> 00:13:41,821
I think that I've fallen in love with the
beautiful assassin who paid me a visit.

271
00:13:43,022 --> 00:13:43,923
Nezumiya?

272
00:13:44,757 --> 00:13:48,127
I procured your cell phone number
from your friends

273
00:13:48,127 --> 00:13:51,297
the ones who were sneaking
around my estate last night.

274
00:13:51,297 --> 00:13:53,232
<i>I'd really like to see you again.</i>

275
00:13:53,232 --> 00:13:54,701
<i>You will come, won't you?</i>

276
00:13:54,901 --> 00:13:58,971
<i>The</i> <i>stars</i> <i>may</i> <i>change,</i> <i>but</i> <i>the</i> <i>importance</i>
<i>of</i> <i>one's</i> <i>friends...</i>

277
00:13:59,238 --> 00:14:00,773
<i>well, that never changes.</i>

278
00:14:01,274 --> 00:14:02,742
<i>Well, I'll be waiting.</i>

279
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:06,345
Hey.

280
00:14:06,913 --> 00:14:08,414
I've made up my mind.

281
00:14:08,581 --> 00:14:10,083
I'm a man, after all.

282
00:14:10,149 --> 00:14:11,784
Even though I can't remember
any of it,

283
00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:13,720
I can't ignore you after
what I did to you.

284
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,623
If you'll settle for a guy like me,
then, please marry me.

285
00:14:29,569 --> 00:14:32,004
What?
Are you serious, Gintoki?

286
00:14:33,439 --> 00:14:34,273
I see.

287
00:14:34,741 --> 00:14:35,942
Then come with me.

288
00:14:36,509 --> 00:14:38,111
Are we going to the wedding hall?

289
00:14:38,111 --> 00:14:39,378
I don't have a lot of money.

290
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:41,681
Just a minute.

291
00:14:42,081 --> 00:14:44,117
<i>This is my first time,</i>
<i>so please be gentle!</i>

292
00:14:44,117 --> 00:14:44,984
Oh, boy.

293
00:14:45,218 --> 00:14:46,853
I'd better watch out for women, too.

294
00:14:47,053 --> 00:14:48,287
Shinpachi!

295
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:50,456
What's wrong?

296
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:51,491
That there!

297
00:14:51,491 --> 00:14:52,492
What the...?

298
00:14:52,759 --> 00:14:54,093
How long has that
hole been here?

299
00:14:54,093 --> 00:14:57,096
Maybe Sacchan is an angel
who came down from the heavens.

300
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:02,902
First off, I need you to meet my father.

301
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:03,970
An introduction, huh?

302
00:15:04,303 --> 00:15:06,706
Well, I've come this far,
so I might as well keep going.

303
00:15:07,273 --> 00:15:09,675
But tell me, why do we have
to get there like this?

304
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:13,079
Well, I was raised in a very strict house,
so I have a curfew.

305
00:15:13,546 --> 00:15:15,982
Wow, you guys sure have a nice,
big house.

306
00:15:16,516 --> 00:15:17,517
Wait, what?

307
00:15:17,517 --> 00:15:18,785
Is your father a scary guy?

308
00:15:18,785 --> 00:15:20,052
What kind of person is he?

309
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:23,756
He's a dishonest, buck‐toothed loan shark
with hair all over his body.

310
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:25,057
What's with that?

311
00:15:25,057 --> 00:15:28,294
Are you at that age when you don't want
to wash your undies in the same load?

312
00:15:28,661 --> 00:15:30,897
Every girl reaches that age eventually.

313
00:15:30,897 --> 00:15:35,735
But listen, try to remember, I mean,
wasn't your father your first love after all?

314
00:15:37,203 --> 00:15:40,907
Hey, once we're newlyweds, I'm going to
change these bad attitude habits of yours!

315
00:15:40,907 --> 00:15:42,341
I'm asserting my dominance!

316
00:15:42,842 --> 00:15:43,709
Be quiet.

317
00:15:44,477 --> 00:15:45,211
Who is that?

318
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:46,913
Our butler, Mr. Smith.

319
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:50,082
He's on the lookout because
I'm late coming home after curfew.

320
00:15:50,516 --> 00:15:52,018
Let me go ahead and tell you.

321
00:15:52,018 --> 00:15:53,619
I'm the type of guy
who's pretty restrictive.

322
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:55,855
If we get married,
I'll bind you to my rules.

323
00:15:57,056 --> 00:15:57,824
Bind me...?

324
00:15:58,424 --> 00:15:59,325
<i>What is this?</i>

325
00:15:59,392 --> 00:16:02,128
<i>Why</i> <i>does</i> <i>the</i> <i>sound</i> <i>of</i> <i>his</i> <i>words</i>
<i>cause</i> <i>my</i> <i>chest</i> <i>to</i> <i>tighten</i> <i>so...?</i>

326
00:16:02,428 --> 00:16:03,896
<i>I want to be bound!
Bind me!</i>

327
00:16:04,130 --> 00:16:05,531
<i>Bind me!</i>
<i>Bind me tighter!</i>

328
00:16:07,834 --> 00:16:08,968
You said that you'll...

329
00:16:09,168 --> 00:16:10,503
you'll bind me, you said?

330
00:16:10,536 --> 00:16:11,671
Damn straight, girl.

331
00:16:11,671 --> 00:16:15,241
Staying out all night with the girlfriends
and mixers will be strictly forbidden!

332
00:16:16,209 --> 00:16:17,176
Mr. Smith saw us.

333
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:21,781
Wha... What's that?

334
00:16:22,014 --> 00:16:22,915
It's the assassin!

335
00:16:22,915 --> 00:16:24,250
The assassin has returned!

336
00:16:25,318 --> 00:16:26,185
Mr. Smith!

337
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,020
That's going too far!

338
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:30,756
Mr. Smith was just doing his job,
for crying out loud!

339
00:16:31,123 --> 00:16:32,892
Looks like a lot are coming.

340
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:34,026
Who are they this time?

341
00:16:34,026 --> 00:16:36,495
It's Mr. Smith B, Smith C,
and Smith D!

342
00:16:36,696 --> 00:16:38,231
Isn't that way too many Mr. Smiths?

343
00:16:38,731 --> 00:16:39,799
It's begun already.

344
00:16:40,099 --> 00:16:41,167
Father is testing the groom.

345
00:16:41,434 --> 00:16:43,102
I need you to fight hard
for the both of us!

346
00:16:44,237 --> 00:16:45,371
Say what?

347
00:16:50,209 --> 00:16:50,910
Let's go now!

348
00:16:51,677 --> 00:16:53,479
Hey!
Don't leave your husband behind!

349
00:16:54,914 --> 00:16:55,882
My report, sir.

350
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:58,451
The assassin woman has broken
through our security

351
00:16:58,451 --> 00:17:00,486
and appears to have entered
the mansion.

352
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:04,090
Then set the traps for them!

353
00:17:04,523 --> 00:17:07,260
And when you find them,
make sure you kill them!

354
00:17:07,493 --> 00:17:08,427
Yes, Sir!

355
00:17:08,794 --> 00:17:11,998
They're just like poor moths flying
into a flame.

356
00:17:15,334 --> 00:17:18,938
They won't make it here without getting
past all the traps I've set for them.

357
00:17:19,505 --> 00:17:24,043
And on the small chance they make it
we have hostages to use as leverage.

358
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:27,046
And then we will finish them off.

359
00:17:30,283 --> 00:17:32,551
Your father must be really strict
for all of this.

360
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:34,186
I'm practically unemployed.

361
00:17:34,186 --> 00:17:34,954
Think that's all right?

362
00:17:34,954 --> 00:17:35,821
It will be fine.

363
00:17:36,122 --> 00:17:37,957
As long as he can trust you
as a person,

364
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:39,058
I'm sure that....

365
00:17:43,129 --> 00:17:43,829
Cliché!

366
00:17:43,829 --> 00:17:45,698
‐This is so cliché, but it's coming!
‐What?

367
00:17:46,666 --> 00:17:48,534
What the hell is going on
at your house?

368
00:17:48,801 --> 00:17:49,869
It's a son‐in‐law test!

369
00:17:50,136 --> 00:17:51,570
He's trying to see if we can
make it together

370
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:53,372
even if the path is closed off.

371
00:17:53,372 --> 00:17:54,807
If the path is closed off?

372
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,509
But that thing is coming right at us!

373
00:17:59,145 --> 00:17:59,879
Step!

374
00:17:59,879 --> 00:18:00,947
And jump!

375
00:18:01,314 --> 00:18:02,415
Go!

376
00:18:03,449 --> 00:18:05,685
It would seems he wants to test
whether or not

377
00:18:05,685 --> 00:18:08,487
you can withstand the pressure
of taking over our house.

378
00:18:08,487 --> 00:18:11,090
Yeah, but I think all I was doing
was running away.

379
00:18:13,059 --> 00:18:14,493
I've been expecting you.

380
00:18:14,794 --> 00:18:15,661
Who's this Smith?

381
00:18:15,661 --> 00:18:16,629
My ex‐boyfriend.

382
00:18:16,696 --> 00:18:18,431
He's working in tandem
with my father

383
00:18:18,431 --> 00:18:20,466
for the purpose
of getting in our way.

384
00:18:20,466 --> 00:18:22,635
Hang on.
You're still seeing your ex‐boyfriend?

385
00:18:22,635 --> 00:18:24,003
I seriously can't allow that.

386
00:18:24,003 --> 00:18:26,072
I said you I'd bind you to my rules.

387
00:18:26,072 --> 00:18:27,006
I know that.

388
00:18:27,006 --> 00:18:28,274
He's a bit of a stalker.

389
00:18:28,574 --> 00:18:29,675
<i>Hasta la vista,</i> baby!

390
00:18:29,675 --> 00:18:31,010
Hey, ex‐boyfriend.

391
00:18:31,143 --> 00:18:33,746
Men who cling on forever
without letting go...

392
00:18:34,714 --> 00:18:36,782
are totally unsophisticated!

393
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:39,318
We need to hurry from here.

394
00:18:39,318 --> 00:18:40,319
Okay!

395
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:45,858
What's going on here?

396
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,060
Who the hell are those guys
chasing us?

397
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,996
‐All my ex‐boyfriends.
‐Wait, what's that?

398
00:18:49,996 --> 00:18:51,330
You're serious?
All of them?

399
00:18:51,330 --> 00:18:53,499
‐Are you trying to make ex‐ball team?
‐This isn't good.

400
00:18:53,499 --> 00:18:56,035
We need to get to father quickly
and explain the situation to him.

401
00:18:56,035 --> 00:18:57,970
All right, in that case,
you go on first!

402
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,472
And I'll catch up later on.

403
00:18:59,939 --> 00:19:01,741
But then, what about you Gin?

404
00:19:01,741 --> 00:19:04,677
In this kind of situation what kind of
husband would leave his wife behind?

405
00:19:05,277 --> 00:19:06,879
Geez, this is hard to run in!

406
00:19:07,279 --> 00:19:08,881
I really should've worn a suit today!

407
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:11,417
Well, I'll leave it to you, then!

408
00:19:11,417 --> 00:19:12,952
Give my regards to your father!

409
00:19:15,054 --> 00:19:17,023
Sure are persistent bastards.

410
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:21,127
Starting right now,
I won't allow you to take...

411
00:19:22,228 --> 00:19:23,963
One more step.

412
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:26,766
On second thought, there's no way
I can do this!

413
00:19:40,346 --> 00:19:41,213
Mr. Ratface!

414
00:19:41,213 --> 00:19:42,782
There's trouble, Mr. Ratface!

415
00:19:42,782 --> 00:19:45,284
The assassin woman has bested
each of our traps,

416
00:19:45,284 --> 00:19:47,386
and she appears to be
heading in this direction.

417
00:19:47,386 --> 00:19:49,422
Most of the assassins
we sent after her

418
00:19:49,422 --> 00:19:50,356
have already been defeated.

419
00:19:50,356 --> 00:19:52,358
That woman doesn't know
when to quit, does she!

420
00:19:52,558 --> 00:19:54,760
Doesn't she care what happens
to the hostages we have?

421
00:19:55,161 --> 00:19:58,197
Now that it's come to this deploy
every last man to stop her!

422
00:19:58,197 --> 00:19:59,131
Get rid of them!

423
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:00,299
‐Yes, Sir!
‐Yes, Sir!

424
00:20:01,801 --> 00:20:02,802
Mr. Ratface!

425
00:20:03,869 --> 00:20:06,372
Their objective is clearly
to rescue the hostages.

426
00:20:06,906 --> 00:20:08,908
I think we should tie
their friends to a post

427
00:20:08,908 --> 00:20:10,910
and spear them to death in
order to keep them away.

428
00:20:11,844 --> 00:20:12,878
Now, then, I will...

429
00:20:13,646 --> 00:20:15,481
Oh my goodness, my glasses.

430
00:20:15,915 --> 00:20:18,017
Hey, where the heck are
you going?

431
00:20:18,484 --> 00:20:19,485
Be quiet.

432
00:20:19,852 --> 00:20:22,088
It is only me, Sacchan is here.

433
00:20:22,521 --> 00:20:25,157
I'll be rescuing you now,
so just play along for a while.

434
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:27,526
There she is!

435
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:28,561
It's the assassin!

436
00:20:28,928 --> 00:20:30,129
Kill her!

437
00:20:30,496 --> 00:20:31,230
‐Sacchan!
‐Sacchan!

438
00:20:31,297 --> 00:20:32,398
‐Run away!
‐Run away!

439
00:20:32,765 --> 00:20:34,366
‐Sacchan!
‐Sacchan!

440
00:20:42,675 --> 00:20:43,509
Who is there?!

441
00:20:55,187 --> 00:20:56,722
The Deadly accurate assassin!

442
00:20:57,022 --> 00:20:58,290
Gin the groom has arrived!

443
00:20:58,591 --> 00:20:59,558
Gin the groom!

444
00:20:59,959 --> 00:21:00,726
Gintoki!

445
00:21:03,896 --> 00:21:04,864
Father!

446
00:21:06,031 --> 00:21:09,635
Let me have your daughter's hand
in marriage!

447
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:25,050
<i>Gin?</i>

448
00:21:25,518 --> 00:21:26,819
<i>Hey, Gintoki!</i>

449
00:21:32,191 --> 00:21:33,692
Can you forgive me Gin?

450
00:21:35,394 --> 00:21:36,595
You see the truth is...

451
00:21:37,663 --> 00:21:39,498
Nothing happened between us.

452
00:21:40,166 --> 00:21:41,167
Yet you...

453
00:21:41,567 --> 00:21:43,769
You still let me use you like this.

454
00:21:44,103 --> 00:21:45,671
Hey, what're you doing?

455
00:21:46,038 --> 00:21:47,373
I'm not even injured right there.

456
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:49,608
Are you listening to me at all?

457
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:51,143
That's enough.

458
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:52,077
Don't touch me.

459
00:21:52,344 --> 00:21:53,546
You reek of natto.

460
00:21:54,346 --> 00:21:57,650
If you can't even treat wounds like this,
no man will ever marry you.

461
00:21:58,117 --> 00:22:00,686
You'll never be someone's wife.
See you.

462
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:02,655
Oh, and one more thing...

463
00:22:03,255 --> 00:22:04,857
The next time you want my help

464
00:22:05,291 --> 00:22:06,692
don't do all this roundabout stuff,

465
00:22:06,692 --> 00:22:08,627
and just come over to Odd Jobs.

466
00:22:13,699 --> 00:22:16,135
I wonder if Sacchan
has fallen in love.

467
00:22:17,436 --> 00:22:19,238
Hard to say, isn't it?

468
00:22:24,977 --> 00:22:27,780
Men really are
such stupid creatures.

469
00:22:30,649 --> 00:22:32,051
<i>Good morning!</i>

470
00:22:32,685 --> 00:22:33,552
Hey, Gin!

471
00:22:33,886 --> 00:22:36,755
You're going to miss Maya Sizitzy's
morning Weather Report...

472
00:22:39,124 --> 00:22:42,127
Now then, Gin, please bind me up
very tightly.

473
00:22:42,428 --> 00:22:43,963
That's not what I meant.

474
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:17,189
<i>Oh! If it isn't Kintoki!</i>

475
00:24:17,222 --> 00:24:19,591
<i>It's me, Tatsuma Sakamoto!</i>

476
00:24:19,925 --> 00:24:22,027
<i>What? A spaceship is</i>
<i>about to crash?</i>

477
00:24:23,128 --> 00:24:24,763
<i>That's certainly terrible!</i>

478
00:24:25,097 --> 00:24:25,831
<i>Next time...</i>

